File: The toddler's aunt found his body, wrapped in a towel. JOHANNESBURG - A childminder who is accused of doing the unthinkable, is expected in court on Monday. The East Rand childminder is accused of murdering a toddler she was entrusted to look after. The grief-stricken parents say she lied about what happened. READ: Nanny arrested for murder of toddler Police say the 51-year-old childminder was arrested after a preliminary investigation linked her to the murder. The nanny had been looking after the child since he was two-months-old, and mostly stayed alone with him while everyone was at work.